                            <comment id="15076170" author="psteitz" created="Thu, 31 Dec 2015 22:22:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in dcd8015fa (master) and 2983ff81b (3_X).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The functions C and N defined by Wilcox have been implemented with recursive definitions unwound.  Using N, exactP has been reimplemented and is now fast enough to extend the small sample range to cover up to 10000 sample product.  This allowed monteCarloP to be eliminated from use by the ksTest default implementation.  That function has been deprecated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
